option.foglooksgoodnow.defaultfogstart.t: Defines the global default fog start value.
option.foglooksgoodnow.defaultfogdensity: Defines the global default fog density value. The fog end is at render distance. At 0, there is no fog.
option.foglooksgoodnow.usecavefog.toolti: Determines whether fog will darken and get more dense when underground.
option.foglooksgoodnow.cavefogdensity.to: Defines the cave fog density value. The fog end is at render distance. At 0, there is no fog.
option.foglooksgoodnow.cavefogcolor.tool: Defines the color of cave fog, in the decimal color format.
If cave fog is active, this will be multiplied with the current fog color.
Determines whether or not the assigned biome uses custom settings.
option.foglooksgoodnow.fogstart.tooltip: Defines the assigned biome's fog start value.
option.foglooksgoodnow.fogdensity.toolti: Defines the assigned biome's fog density value. The fog end is at render distance. At 0, there is no fog.
option.foglooksgoodnow.fogcolor.tooltip: Defines the color of biome fog, in the decimal color format.
option.foglooksgoodnow.overridecolors.to: Determines whether or not this biome's fog colors are overriden by "Biome Fog Color".
